node.text:
I have been working on my new brand @kfourthirteenbrand for the past 5 months I finally started vlogging back in April & putting in the work to get things done‼️This has been so much on me & I didn’t even launch yet lol. But im so excited to announce what my new brand is about. I finally can say im wearing MY OWN brand hair when people ask 🥺😇😇 I am so blessed to be able to start my own brand with something I’ve always wanted to do. I ordered hair from a vendor 3 years ago & then realized how expensive the business was gonna be I was only 18/19 & wasn’t making enough to start a hair business 🥲 Now im 22 & can do what I had a passion for from the jump 🙏🏽 everything happens at the right time for you! 

Thank you to EVERYONE who genuinely supports me & has watched me grow these last couple of years🤍 I love my true supporters, I wouldn’t be able to have half the things I obtained without the support‼️ 

Sign up for my site to get more info on my launch & $$$ off on different items. COMMENT down below something from @lashaiilax that y’all loved for me to bring back 👀👀

node.text: This is very hard for me to watch, it’s the simple fact people can be so EVIL!!!!! This is only a 2minute video of just SOME of these incidents, there are 20497473737 more that were either not recorded or been recorded but not yet have been seen. It is so sad that this has been going on for YEARS & there has been no change. These “peaceful” protest are not working, no one hears a baby until they start crying & throwing a fit... so be it. All of those who are against the protest & riots need to step a side, your opinion is not needed. Go sit with the racist & evil people who abuse your own people, just a disappointment. Us black people need to stick together, no one else has us or knows our struggle as black people like WE DO! It angers me even more to see BLACK MALE police officers act in such rage. These white people do not care about us at all so to try to please them is beyond me, who makes them superior?!? White people have too much power, fight back. A lot of people’s true colors are showing right now, if you losing “friends” oh mf well! Im so sorry to anyone who has lost someone due to police brutality or due to an act of a racist person. All these people crying over stores is NOT the time right now F*CK the stores! They can be replaced!!!! Lives can not, it’s not me being “ignorant” but these are materialistic things & if a store was somebody’s ONLY income... you are taught to always have a back up plan, savings, insurance ETC for times like this!!! People are being BEAT & MURDERED that is something that should make you cry & angry! I love being black & I hate seeing other BLACK people try to please the white man, such a disappointment. I love black men I just want them to see the value they have & to be safe out here!!🖤 #policebrutality #blacklivesmatter #nojusticenopeace #rip

node.text:
I really missed shipping out my products to y’all 🥺 I took a break on my first business & popped back out with @kfourthirteenbrand 🦋 

For those trying to shop, you missed the presale. Launch date for everyone to shop coming soon 🙏🏽✨ Thank you to those who shopped for the presale & been very patient with the delays due to certain things.

Monday & yesterday was so hectic!! I vlogged so you all can see everything on @kfourthirteenbrand YouTube channel🎥🖥 

I put my all into my brand & basically anything I do. It can be very draining at times but I never give up on anything that I set my mind to. Don’t let anyone discourage you from your goals. Patience is key🙏🏽 You can’t rush what’s meant to be. 

Im so excited to launch because due to me waiting on certain items I was able to come up with some amazing ideas to add to my brand! 🥰🥰 

Thank you all again see y’all on the order list once @kfourthirteenbrand actually drops 👏🏽
